        q: `A 3-year-old boy has a poor appetite and is underweight for his age and height. Physical examination shows hepatosplenomegaly. The hemoglobin concentration is 6 g/dL (10.5–13.5 g/dL), and the peripheral blood smear shows severely hypochromic and microcytic RBCs. The total serum iron level is normal, and the reticulocyte count is 5% (0.5–1.5 %). A radiograph of the skull shows maxillofacial deformities and expanded marrow spaces. Which of the following is the most likely cause of this child’s illness?`,
