        q: `A 23-year-old woman in her 25th week of pregnancy has felt no fetal movement for the past 3 days. Three weeks later, she still has not given birth and suddenly develops dyspnea with cyanosis. On physical examination, her temperature is 37&#176; C, pulse is 106 beats/min, respirations are 23 breaths/min, and blood pressure is 80/40 mm Hg. She has large ecchymoses over the skin of her entire body. A stool sample is positive for occult blood. Laboratory studies show an elevated prothrombin time and partial thromboplastin time. The platelet count is decreased, plasma fibrinogen is markedly decreased, and fibrin split products are detected. A blood culture is negative. Which of the following is the most likely cause of her bleeding diathesis?`,
