        q: `A 67-year-old man has a 5-month history of increasing weakness, fatigue, and weight loss. He now has decreasing vision in both eyes and has headaches and dizziness. His hands are sensitive to cold. On physical examination, he has generalized lymphadenopathy and hepatosplenomegaly. Laboratory studies demonstrate a serum protein level of 9.5 g/dL (7–18 g/dL) and albumin concentration of 3.2 g/dL (3.5–5.5 g/dL). A bone marrow biopsy is performed, and microscopic examination of the specimen shows infiltration by numerous small plasmacytoid lymphoid cells. Which of the following additional laboratory findings is most likely to be reported for this patient?`,
